snippet: The United States Navy’s Joint Typhoon Warning Center in Hawaii said the typhoon, Haiyan, had maximum sustained winds of 195 miles per hour, with gusts up to 235 m.p.h.
abstract: Super Typhoon Haiyan, one of the strongest typhoons in recent history, rips through the Philippines, killing at least one person, cutting communications, snapping off roofs and putting millions of people at risk.
lead_paragraph: The United States Navy’s Joint Typhoon Warning Center in Hawaii said the typhoon, Haiyan, had maximum sustained winds of 195 miles per hour, with gusts up to 235 m.p.h.
